…gives Kano govt 24-hour ultimatum Deposed Emir of Kano, Muhammad Sanusi II, on Tuesday, gave the Kano State Government a 24-hour ultimatum to release him or face legal action. Sanusi’s lawyer, Abubakar Mahmoud (SAN), disclosed this during a press conference in his chamber in Kano. Mahmoud warned that the Kano State Government risked being dragged to court if Sanusi was not released within 24 hours. The deposed monarch’s lawyer, therefore, urged the Inspector General of Police, the Director General of the Department of State Services, and the Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice to ensure his immediate release. 